No. Never entered my mind.

157
00:11:46,998 --> 00:11:49,910
怎麼了？你失望了嗎？
Why? Are you disappointed?

158
00:11:51,002 --> 00:11:52,583
一點也不！
Not in the least!

159
00:11:53,171 --> 00:11:55,287
事實上，我鬆了口氣。哦。
In fact, I'm relieved. Oh.

160
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:56,917
那很好。
That's good.

161
00:11:57,008 --> 00:11:59,420
所以你過了有趣的一天，是嗎？
So you had an interesting day, huh?

162
00:11:59,802 --> 00:12:01,212
想談談嗎？
Care to talk about it?

163
00:12:01,638 --> 00:12:03,219
嗯，讓我想想。
Well, let's see.

164
00:12:03,306 --> 00:12:05,217
今天早上我去購物了
This morning I went shopping

165
00:12:05,308 --> 00:12:08,300
然後我去了現代藝術博物館。
and then I went to the museum of modern art.

166
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:10,385
那裏有個極好的新展覽。
They have a marvelous new exhibit there.

167
00:12:10,772 --> 00:12:13,434
然後我在，嗯，廣場大飯店吃了午飯。
Then I had lunch at the, uh, Plaza.

168
00:12:13,524 --> 00:12:14,684
棕櫚庭。
The palm court.

169
00:12:14,776 --> 00:12:16,516
班尼迪克蛋。
Eggs Benedict.

170
00:12:16,611 --> 00:12:19,819
然後，在三點前幾分鐘
And then, a few minutes before 3 o'clock

171
00:12:19,906 --> 00:12:22,147
我搶劫了我丈夫的銀行。
I stuck up my husband's bank.

172
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:38,121
你睡着了嗎？
Are you asleep?

173
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,256
不，我...
No, I...

174
00:12:40,343 --> 00:12:43,210
你沒有聯想。你——你知道嗎？
You're not associating. You-you realize that?

175
00:12:43,304 --> 00:12:44,760
你是什麼意思？
How do you mean?

176
00:12:44,847 --> 00:12:45,908
我是說，你說你去購物。
I mean, you said you went shopping.

177
00:12:45,932 --> 00:12:47,243
你去了博物館，你吃了午飯。
You went to the museum, you had lunch.

178
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:48,757
嗯哼。
Mm-hmm.

179
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:51,809
然後你說了些完全無關的話。
And then you said something entirely irrelevant.

180
00:12:51,896 --> 00:12:54,603
Gregory，不是我不聯想，而是你。
Gregory, it's you who's not associating.

181
00:12:54,691 --> 00:12:56,807
我只是說我搶了我丈夫的銀行。
All I said was I stuck up my husband's bank.

182
00:12:56,901 --> 00:12:58,892
你又說了一遍。但你不可能那樣做。
You said it again. But you couldn't possibly.

183
00:12:58,987 --> 00:12:59,987
你怎麼知道？
How do you know?

184
00:13:00,071 --> 00:13:01,674
因爲我當了你三年的分析師。
Because I've been your analyst for three years.

185
00:13:01,698 --> 00:13:02,841
我知道你能做什麼
I know what you're capable of

186
00:13:02,865 --> 00:13:04,526
也知道你做不到什麼。
and I know what you're not capable of.

187
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:05,617
你想打賭嗎？
Would you like to bet?

188
00:13:05,702 --> 00:13:07,112
我在精神病學界的聲譽
My reputation in psychiatry

189
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:08,943
對你願意拿出的任何東西。
against anything you care to put up.

190
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:10,949
這些夠嗎？
Will this be enough?

191
00:13:12,292 --> 00:13:13,407
那是什麼？
What's that?

192
00:13:14,335 --> 00:13:16,542
嗯，我想那叫贓款。
Well, I think it's called the loot.

193
00:13:17,005 --> 00:13:19,542
贓——款？
The-the loot?

194
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:21,793
佩—— Penelope，你能...
P-Penelope, would-would you...

195
00:13:27,807 --> 00:13:30,469
所以你認爲你搶了銀行，是嗎？
So you think you robbed a bank, huh?

196
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,767
嗯，我一直這麼說。
Hm, I've been saying that.

197
00:13:32,854 --> 00:13:35,140
然後我去了伯格多夫，買了這套新裝。
Then I went over to Bergdorf's and bought this new outfit.

198
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:36,767
你喜歡嗎？
Do you like it?

199
00:13:36,858 --> 00:13:39,144
Penelope，你是要我相信
Penelope, do you expect me to believe

200
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:41,066
你搶了你丈夫的銀行
that you robbed your husband's bank

201
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:42,815
然後輕鬆地去伯格多夫
and went blithely off to Bergdorf's

202
00:13:42,905 --> 00:13:45,612
把贓款花在裙子和貂皮上？
and spent the loot on dresses and minks?

203
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:47,941
- 當然不會。 - 那就好。
- Of course not. - Well, thank goodness.

204
00:13:48,036 --> 00:13:50,152
不，我不會花贓款。
No, I wouldn't spend stolen money.

205
00:13:50,246 --> 00:13:51,406
我有賒賬賬戶。
I have a charge account.

206
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:52,862
你仍然堅持你搶了銀行。
You still insist you robbed a bank.

207
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:54,322
那你怎麼可能呢？
Now how could you?

208
00:13:54,417 --> 00:13:55,873
Gregory，這很簡單...
Gregory, it's very simple...

209
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,813
拜託，我——我不想聽。
我——不想聽。
Please, I-I don't wanna hear. I-I don't want to hear it.

210
00:13:57,837 --> 00:13:59,919
我我我我不想聽這件事。
I-I-I-I don't wanna hear about it.

211
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:03,631
哦，當然，那會使你成爲事後從犯。
Oh, of course, that would make you an accessory after the fact.

212
00:14:03,718 --> 00:14:06,255
Gregory，對不起。
別不高興。
Gregory, I'm sorry. Don't be upset.

213
00:14:06,346 --> 00:14:08,428
我們就忘了我曾提起過這事。
We'll just forget I ever mentioned it.

214
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:10,596
我們什麼都不會忘的。
We're not going to forget about anything.

215
00:14:12,477 --> 00:14:14,263
你——你搶了多少錢？
H-how much did you get?

216
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:18,391
太可怕了！
That's horrible!

217
00:14:18,483 --> 00:14:19,848
是啊，但我剛數過了。
Yeah, but I just counted it.

218
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:21,478
只有略多於6萬美元。
It's only a little over 60,000.

219
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:23,025
所以也就只有一半那麼可怕。
So it's only half as horrible.

220
00:14:23,112 --> 00:14:24,715
Penelope，你的生活就像一場瘋狂的魔術表演一樣不可思議。
Penelope, nobody can just walk into a bank

221
00:14:24,739 --> 00:14:27,151
並且通過開口要來 $60,000。
and pick up $60,000 by asking for it.

222
00:14:27,241 --> 00:14:29,823
當然可以。前提是你有槍。
Of course, you can. If you have a gun.

223
00:14:29,911 --> 00:14:31,276
你根本沒有槍！
You don't own a gun!

224
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:33,828
哦，Gregory，你總是這麼樂觀。
Oh, Gregory, you're always so positive.

225
00:14:33,915 --> 00:14:35,184
你以爲這是什麼？
What do you think this is?

226
00:14:36,292 --> 00:14:39,750
哦，對不起。我不知道它是上膛的。
Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't know it was loaded.

227
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:41,748
我是在哪家五金店買的。
I bought it in the five and dime.

228
00:14:42,799 --> 00:14:47,042
Penelope，這對你的治療非常不利。
Penelope, this is very bad for your therapy.

229
00:14:47,136 --> 00:14:49,001
對不起，Gregory。
I'm sorry, Gregory.

230
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:56,430
在你的分析中，我顯然在某處……
Somewhere in your analysis, I have obviously...

231
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:01,021
錯過了一個重要的線索。
Passed up a vital clue.

232
00:15:01,109 --> 00:15:05,944
現在我——我要你從頭再告訴我一次
Now I-I want you to tell me again from the beginning

233
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:08,112
關於你第一次拿走東西的那次。
about the first time that you took something.

234
00:15:10,034 --> 00:15:12,946
你是說偷東西，不是嗎？
You mean stole something, don't you?

235
00:15:13,037 --> 00:15:14,823
Gregory，我們不如面對現實。
Gregory, we might as well face it.

236
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:16,120
我是個偷竊狂。
I'm a kleptomaniac.

237
00:15:16,207 --> 00:15:19,324
我拒絕從臨牀上接受那個詞。
I refuse to accept that word clinically.

238
00:15:19,419 --> 00:15:23,662
那第一次是什麼時候？
Now what was the first time?

239
00:15:25,258 --> 00:15:29,342
嗯，真正的第一次……
Well, the very first time...

240
00:15:29,429 --> 00:15:31,886
是在我大學的最後一週。
Was my last week in college.

241
00:15:31,973 --> 00:15:33,964
我盛裝打扮去參加畢業舞會，
I was all dressed up for the senior prom

242
00:15:34,058 --> 00:15:36,390
這時 Klobb 教授過來了。
when Professor Klobb came by.

243
00:15:36,477 --> 00:15:39,310
Klobb 教授教人類學404。
Professor Klobb taught anthropology 404.

244
00:15:39,397 --> 00:15:41,197
他說他想在實驗室裏給我看一些照片，
And he said he'd like to show me some pictures

245
00:15:41,232 --> 00:15:43,314
是關於 Okokos 部落的。
of the Okokos tribe in his laboratory.

246
00:15:45,695 --> 00:15:49,028
他說 Okokos 有些非常奇怪的習俗。
He said the Okokos had some very strange customs.

247
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:51,989
嗯，他們確實有，
Well, they certainly did,

248
00:15:52,076 --> 00:15:53,987
但也不比 Klobb 教授的奇怪。
but no stranger than Professor Klobb's.

249
00:16:05,715 --> 00:16:07,125
哦！哦！
Oh! Oh!

250
00:16:08,176 --> 00:16:09,586
哦！
Oh!

251
00:16:15,099 --> 00:16:16,305
哦！
Oh!

252
00:16:16,392 --> 00:16:17,677
抱歉。
Sorry.

253
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:24,347
哦！
Oh!

254
00:16:31,532 --> 00:16:32,897
啊！
Ah!

255
00:17:07,318 --> 00:17:09,104
起初我並沒有注意到，
I didn't notice it at first,

256
00:17:09,195 --> 00:17:11,356
但我的手裏有了東西。
but there was something in my hand.

257
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:13,187
不知怎的，在我們的課間裏，
Somehow, sometime during our session

258
00:17:13,282 --> 00:17:14,818
在原始人類學那節課上，
in primitive anthropology,

259
00:17:14,909 --> 00:17:16,524
我抓住了 Klobb 教授的
I had grabbed hold of Professor Klobb's

260
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:19,281
懷錶鏈，鑲着鑽石的。
watch fob, diamond-studded.

261
00:17:19,372 --> 00:17:21,112
我本來可以把它送回去，當然，
I could have sent it back, of course,

262
00:17:21,207 --> 00:17:22,697
但我決定就留着它，
but I decided I'd just keep it

263
00:17:22,792 --> 00:17:26,159
作爲奧科科斯部落那些奇怪習俗的紀念。
in memory of the strange customs of the Okokos tribe.

264
00:17:26,254 --> 00:17:29,621
這就是我犯罪生涯的開始。
So that's where I began my life of crime.

265
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:31,330
幾乎是偶然的。
Practically by accident.

266
00:17:35,471 --> 00:17:37,382
下一次事件是什麼時候？
When was the next incident?

267
00:17:38,099 --> 00:17:39,930
剛來紐約時有些零零碎碎的事，
Well, there were some odds and ends

268
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:41,848
那是在我剛到紐約的時候。
when I first came to New York.

269
00:17:41,936 --> 00:17:45,178
但在遇到 James 之後，我再也沒有偷過東西。
But then after I met James, I never stole anything.

270
00:17:46,941 --> 00:17:49,182
直到……直到什麼時候？
Until... until when?

271
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:52,147
直到我的婚禮那天。
Until my wedding day.

272
00:17:59,036 --> 00:18:01,903
我永遠忘不了那天 James 看起來有多英俊。
I'll never forget how handsome James looked that day.

273
00:18:04,959 --> 00:18:07,120
我當時非常地愛他。
I was terribly in love with him.

274
00:18:07,211 --> 00:18:10,169
但看起來，我的伴娘 Mildred Halliday 也是如此。
But so, it seems, was my matron of honor, Mildred Halliday.

275
00:18:10,256 --> 00:18:11,871
她並非我親自選的，
She wasn't exactly my choice,

276
00:18:11,966 --> 00:18:13,686
只是她的父親是那家銀行的董事會成員。
but her father was on the board of the bank.

277
00:18:16,887 --> 00:18:19,344
在招待會上，James 突然消失了。
At the reception, James suddenly disappeared.

278
00:18:27,148 --> 00:18:28,433
後來當我回想時，
When I came to think about it,

279
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:30,936
我好像也找不到 Mildred。
I couldn't seem to locate Mildred either.

280
00:18:31,027 --> 00:18:32,892
我當時並不懷疑，真的，
I wasn't suspicious, really,

281
00:18:32,987 --> 00:18:34,978
但我開始懷疑這件事也許並非不可能。
but I began to wonder if it wasn't just possible.

282
00:18:36,657 --> 00:18:37,692
果然如此。
It was.

283
00:18:38,993 --> 00:18:40,483
在這種情況下，
In situations like this,

284
00:18:40,578 --> 00:18:43,035
我總會想出一些巧妙的話來說。
I always think of clever things to say.

285
00:18:43,122 --> 00:18:44,737
好了，該切蛋糕了。
Well, time to cut the cake.

286
00:18:44,832 --> 00:18:46,538
你好，Penelope。
Hello, Penelope.

287
00:18:46,626 --> 00:18:48,912
Jimmy 和我剛纔在談婚禮的事。
Jimmy and I were just discussing weddings.

288
00:18:49,003 --> 00:18:51,119
是的，我聽見了你們。
Yes, I heard you.

289
00:18:51,505 --> 00:18:53,166
大家總是親新娘，
Well, everybody always kisses the bride,

290
00:18:53,257 --> 00:18:55,748
但——沒人想到新郎。
but-but-but no one thinks of the groom.

291
00:18:55,843 --> 00:18:57,049
除了你。
Except you.

292
00:18:57,136 --> 00:18:59,377
嗯，這是我的慷慨本性。
Well, it's my generous nature.

293
00:18:59,472 --> 00:19:02,555
哦，Jim，Jim，看看，你臉上全是口紅。
Oh, Jim, Jim, look. You're all over lipstick.

294
00:19:05,353 --> 00:19:06,718
哦，別吃醋，親愛的。
Oh, don't be jealous, love.

295
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:09,519
Jimmy 和我認識很久了。
Jimmy and I have known each other for ages.

296
00:19:09,607 --> 00:19:10,642
謝謝。
Ta.

297
00:19:12,485 --> 00:19:13,645
謝謝。
Ta.

298
00:19:15,738 --> 00:19:18,070
我曾一度想背後捅她一刀，
I thought briefly about stabbing her in the back,

299
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:20,489
但我怕蛋糕刀不夠鋒利。
but I was afraid the cake knife wasn't sharp enough.

300
00:19:20,576 --> 00:19:22,692
你想要解釋一下嗎？
Would you care for an explanation?

301
00:19:23,663 --> 00:19:25,995
不用，你不必這樣做。
No, you don't have to.

302
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:28,452
感覺如何？
How was it?

303
00:19:31,629 --> 00:19:33,961
我可以接受也可以不接受。
I could take it or leave it.

304
00:19:34,048 --> 00:19:36,004
你把她的口紅都擦掉了嗎？
Have you got all of her lipstick off?

305
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:38,253
希望沒有。怎麼了？
No, I hope. Why?

306
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:53,063
那時候，沒人會懷疑 James 是個銀行家。
In those days, you'd never suspect James was a banker.

307
00:19:54,068 --> 00:19:57,105
準備好了，大家，準備！他們來了！
Ready, everybody, ready! Here they come!

308
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:59,812
好啦，Penelope，讓我們看看你能不能擊中未來的新娘。
Alright, Penelope, let's see you hit a future bride.

309
00:20:03,828 --> 00:20:05,989
我仍然記得 Mildred 仰望我的樣子。
I can still see Mildred looking up at me.

310
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:08,162
她戴着綠寶石的耳環和項鍊，
She was wearing her emerald earrings and necklace,

311
00:20:08,249 --> 00:20:10,285
還有一副極爲高傲的表情。
plus a very superior expression.

312
00:20:12,086 --> 00:20:14,077
到了拋新娘花束的時候了。
It was time to toss the wedding bouquet.

313
00:20:15,798 --> 00:20:17,254
我決定讓 Mildred 抓到它。
I decided I'd let Mildred have it.

314
00:20:19,093 --> 00:20:21,505
哦，Mildred。
Oh, Mildred.

315
00:20:21,595 --> 00:20:23,927
哦，親愛的，真是太抱歉了。
Oh, darling, I'm terribly sorry.

316
00:20:25,307 --> 00:20:27,673
哦，那太好了，親愛的。
Oh, that's good, darling.

317
00:20:27,768 --> 00:20:29,053
謝謝。
Ta.

318
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:33,099
- 再見，我的愛。 - 再見。
- Goodbye, my love. - Goodbye.

319
00:20:33,190 --> 00:20:34,430
而——親愛的，親愛的，
And-and-and, darling, darling,

320
00:20:34,525 --> 00:20:37,107
請不要忘了從此過上幸福快樂的生活。
please don't forget to live happily ever after.

321
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,981
- 我會的，再見。再見。 - 再見，James。
- I will, bye. Bye. - Goodbye, James.

322
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:41,687
- 再見，Douglas。 - 再見！
- Goodbye, Douglas. - Bye!

323
00:20:44,118 --> 00:20:47,451
我的，我的耳環。我的耳環！
My, my earrings. My earrings!

324
00:20:47,538 --> 00:20:50,029
當我們十天後回家時，
And when we returned home ten days later,

325
00:20:50,124 --> 00:20:53,241
項鍊和耳環仍然在盆栽棕櫚的罐子裏。
the necklace and earrings were still in the potted palm jar.

326
00:20:53,335 --> 00:20:56,953
- 你從未歸還它們嗎？ - 沒有。我爲什麼要還？
